{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Magby}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=239|prev=Elekid|nextnum=241|next=Miltank|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Magby\n|jname=ブビィ\n|jtranslit=Bubyi\n|tmname=Buby\n|ndex=240\n|oldjdex=150\n|jdex=152\n|sdex=200\n|u2dex=053\n|adex=166\n|abrow=073\n|obrow=187\n|opbrow=074\n|type1=Fire\n|category=Live Coal\n|height-ftin=2\'04"\n|height-m=0.7\n|weight-lbs=47.2\n|weight-kg=21.4\n|ability1=Flame Body\n|abilityd=Vital Spirit\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Undiscovered\n|eggcycles=25\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|expyield=73\n|oldexp=117\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=63\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|body=06\n|pokefordex=magby\n|generation=2\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Magby\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ブビィ\'\'\' \'\'Buby\'\') is a {{type|Fire}} [[baby Pokémon]] introduced in [[Generation II]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Magmar}} starting at [[level]] 30, which evolves into {{p|Magmortar}} when [[trade]]d holding a [[Magmarizer]].\n\n==Biology==\nMagby is a bipedal Pokémon that has a red body with a yellow, flame-shaped marking on its stomach. Its head is covered with large lumps, and it has a rounded, yellow beak. There is a single spike on its back and it has a tapered tail. Its short arms have three clawed fingers, while its feet have only two clawed toes. Magby can breathe 1100&nbsp;°F (600&nbsp;°C) flames, and hot embers drip from its mouth. Its health is determined by these flames. Yellow flames show that a Magby is in good health, while flames mixed with a lot of smoke is symptomatic of fatigue, and flames dripping from its nose is a sign of a cold. Magby\'s {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Mountain Pokémon|volcanic}} habitat ensures its health. However, it [[PK07|can be seen]] living in towns.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Roland Magby.png|thumb|left|250px|Magby in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n[[File:Magby Egg.png|left|thumb|200px|A Magby {{pkmn|Egg}} in the anime]]\n===Major appearances===\nMagby debuted in \'\'[[PK07|Pikachu & Pichu]]\'\' as one of the [[Pichu Brothers]]\' friends. It made further appearances in \'\'[[Trouble in Big Town]]\'\', \'\'[[HS06|Of Meowth]] [[HS07|and Pokémon]]\'\', \'\'[[HS09|Big Meowth]]\'\', \'\'[[HS10|Little Dreams]]\'\', and \'\'[[Pichu Bros. in Party Panic]]\'\'; and it also made a brief cameo appearance in \'\'[[M11|Giratina and the Sky Warrior]]\'\'.\n\nMagby made its main series debut in \'\'[[EP262|You\'re A Star, Larvitar]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Satchel]]. Satchel was trying to get it to evolve into {{p|Magmar}} in time for the [[Silver Conference]], and he eventually succeeded. It reappeared in [[EP263|the next episode]], where it was part of an {{p|Unown}}\'s dimension.\n\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[AG015|Gonna Rule The School!]]\'\', under the ownership of the [[Pokémon Trainers\' School]]. {{OBP|Tommy|AG015}}, a student of the school, was {{pkmn|training}} with it. He used Magby during a battle against [[Max]], who was training a {{p|Poliwag}}.\n\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[DP170|An Elite Coverup!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Roland]]. It had been captured by {{TRT}}, who tricked Roland into thinking they could help raise it and evolve it. However, it was eventually rescued.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[AG010|You Said a Mouthful!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Anthony|AG010}}. It was kept inside {{p|Pelipper}}\'s beak as an effective way to use its attacks to defeat Pokémon, which included [[Ash\'s Taillow]] and a Trainer\'s {{p|Zigzagoon}}.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Magby appeared in \'\'[[AG159|Off the Unbeaten Path]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the [[Pokémon Orienteering]] competition.\n\nA Magby appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[DP020|Mutiny in the Bounty!]]\'\' as one of [[J]]\'s captured Pokémon.\n\nA {{pkmn|Coordinator}}\'s Magby appeared in \'\'[[DP146|Dressed for Jess Success!]]\'\', where it was seen participating in the {{to|Lilypad}} {{pkmn|Contest}}.\n\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[DP160|A Marathon Rivalry!]]\'\', under the ownership of a competitor in the [[Pokéathlon]] held in [[Camellia Town]].\n\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[M20|I Choose You!]]\'\', where it was playfully chasing a {{p|Chikorita}}.\n\nA Trainer\'s Magby appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'. It was seen using {{m|Flamethrower}} during the [[Alola Bread Festival]].\n\nSix Trainers\' Magby appeared in \'\'[[M21|The Power of Us]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Johto}}\n{{Animedexbody|EP262|Magby|Ash\'s Pokédex|Magby, the Live Coal Pokémon. Magby is the [[Baby Pokémon|pre-evolved form]] of {{p|Magmar}}. Despite its small [[List of Pokémon by height|size]], it is a tough opponent and produces an extremely hot flame.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|original|Johto}}\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP170|Magby|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Magby, the Live Coal Pokémon. Magby has a magma-like substance in its body, and it emits super-fiery breath.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Whitney Magby Golden Boys.png|thumb|200px|Magby in [[Pokémon Gold & Silver: The Golden Boys]]]]\n[[File:Day-Care Couple Magby Cleffa Adventures.png|thumb|left|200px|Magby in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Magical Pokémon Journey manga===\n[[Kiaraway]], a Trainer who specializes in collecting Fire-type Pokémon, owns a Magby. It is seen once in \'\'[[PPP50|Vulpix and Cyndaquil]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Magby is one of the baby Pokémon that escape from the Daycare Center near [[Goldenrod City]] in \'\'[[PS107|Gligar Glide]]\'\'.\n\nLater, in \'\'[[PS121|Off Course with Corsola]]\'\', a Magby was one of the Pokémon {{adv|Crystal}} {{pkmn2|caught}} and sent to {{adv|Professor Oak}} via the Portable Transfer System.\n\nA Magby appeared in \'\'[[PS179|The Last Battle XIII]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon sent to participate in the fight in [[Ilex Forest]].\n\n{{adv|Pearl}} fights multiple Magby at [[Fuego Ironworks]] left behind by [[Team Galactic]] in \'\'[[PS384|Maddening Magby]]\'\'.\n\nA Magby appeared in a picture in \'\'[[PAORAS04|Omega Alpha Adventure 4]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Gold & Silver: The Golden Boys manga===\n[[Whitney]] owns a Magby in [[Pokémon Gold & Silver: The Golden Boys]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Magby appears in \'\'[[PM074|Clefairy Becomes a Father...?!]]\'\' along with its evolved form where it took on {{p|Cleffa}}.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Magby (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Fire}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=II}}\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=II|reg1=Johto|num1=150}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Gold|entry=Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Silver|entry=It is found in volcanic craters. Its body temp. is over {{tt|1100 degrees|600°C}}, so don\'t under-estimate it.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Crystal|entry=It naturally spits an {{tt|1100-degree|600°C}} flame. It is said when many appear, it heralds a volcanic eruption.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Stadium 2|t=FFF|color=000|entry=Each and every time it inhales and exhales, hot embers dribble out of its mouth and nostrils.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=III|reg1=Hoenn|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Ruby|v2=Sapphire|t=FFF|t2=FFF|entry=Magby\'s state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Emerald|t=FFF|entry=If a Magby is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=FireRed|entry=It is found in volcanic craters. Its body heat exceeds {{tt|1,100 degrees F|600 degrees C}}, so don\'t underestimate it.}}\n{{Dex